at": "2020-06-26T17:41:26Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "On Unix receiving to a buffer shorter than the incoming payload silently truncates the read. On Windows the read is completed but an error is returned. Not being that familiar with Windows I found this behaviour surprising.\r\n\r\nThe following comment in [`sys/windows/net.rs`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/1d834550d54e4c5211f03f877c1756425f24be98/src/libstd/sys/windows/net.rs#L204-L205) suggests that making Unix and Windows behave the same is (at times) a goal of the standard library:\r\n```\r\n        // On unix when a socket is shut down all further reads return 0, so we\r\n        // do the same on windows to map a shut down socket to returning EOF.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf it is I'd like to propose that `WSAEMSGSIZE` be absorbed so that both platforms behave the same.", "closed_by": {"login": "andrewtj", "id": 21676, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxNjc2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/21676?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj", "html_url": "https://github.com/andrewtj", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewtj/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/55794/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0,